      <body>From the docs:

    &lt;%= render :layout =&gt; &quot;my_layout&quot; do |customer| %&gt;
      Hello &lt;%= customer.name %&gt;
    &lt;% end %&gt;
    
    # The layout
    &lt;html&gt;
      &lt;%= yield Struct.new(:name).new(&quot;David&quot;) %&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;

This does not work as expected, the content inside the render block is not being generated.
By using yield without any param, the content is generated, but no variable is available.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the docs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;%= render :layout =&amp;gt; &quot;my_layout&quot; do |customer| %&amp;gt;
  Hello &amp;lt;%= customer.name %&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;% end %&amp;gt;

# The layout
&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;%= yield Struct.new(:name).new(&quot;David&quot;) %&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This does not work as expected, the content inside the render
block is not being generated.&lt;br&gt;
By using yield without any param, the content is generated, but no
variable is available.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
